22/04/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski began political consultations Thursday (21 April) on amending the constitution. The first meeting was with VMRO-People's Party leader Vesna Janevska, and in the weeks ahead Buckovski will approach all the other parties in parliament. The changes the government wants to initiate are related to judicial reform and strengthening the independence of the courts, as well as elections legislation incorporating observations made by international monitors during the recent local vote. (MIA, Makfax - 21/04/05) 
